      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
         <p>Marie Dye received three degrees from the University of Chicago: Bachelor of Science (1914), Master of Science (1917), Doctor of Philosophy (1922). She taught at Michigan State University from 1922 to 1956.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Correspondence, reports and photographs used by Marie Dye to write a book titled, "History of the Department of Home Economics, University of Chicago" (1972).</p>
      </scopecontent>
